The Planning Domain Definition Language (PDDL) [1] builds upon and extends the
STRIPS representation, providing a more expressive and standardized syntax for a wider range
of classical planning problems. In PDDL:

• Domain File defines:
– Types: Categories for objects (e.g., block, robot).
– Predicates: Relations or properties (e.g., (on ?x - block ?y - block)).
– Action Schemas: Templates for actions, generalizing STRIPS operators. For instance:

